### 1. Login (Standard)
# Ce endpoint utilise maintenant votre serializer personnalisé "MyTokenObtainPairSerializer".
# Il devrait retourner "access", "refresh" ET "user_data" (token decodé).
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/token/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "your_password"
}

### 2. Refresh Token
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/token/refresh/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh": "your_refresh_token_here"
}

### 3. Properties List
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/properties/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer your_access_token_here

### 4. Register (NEW)
# Ce endpoint permet de créer un compte.
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/register/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "newuser",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123",
  "first_name": "New",
  "last_name": "User",
  "role": "client"
}

### 5. Get User Profile (NEW)
# Récupère les infos de l'utilisateur connecté via le token.
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/me/
Authorization: Bearer your_access_token_here
